Info2: <<
Package: sipclient
Version: 0.2.1
Revision: 1
Distribution: 10.5
Type: python (2.5)
Description: Python SIP client based on PJSIP
License: GPL
Maintainer: Ruud Klaver <ruud@ag-projects.com>

# Dependencies:
Depends: python25, dnspython-py25, lxml-py25, python-application-py25, python-xcaplib-py25, setuptools-py25

# Unpack Phase:
Source: http://download.ag-projects.com/SipClient/sipclient_%v.tar.gz
Source-MD5: 9d7804cd5ea6bc1e4b8b61cdd795341a
SourceDirectory: sipclient-%v

# Compile Phase:
CompileScript: <<
#!/bin/bash -ev
rm pjsip
sed -i "" -e sX/usr/XX pypjua/clients/setupconfig.py
svn co http://svn.pjsip.org/repos/pjproject/trunk pjsip
cd pjsip
./configure
make
cd ..
./build_inplace
python2.5 setup.py build
<<
# Install Phase:
InstallScript: python2.5 setup.py install --root=%d
DocFiles: README AUTHORS docs/* debian/changelog config.ini.sample

# Additional Info:
DescDetail: <<
SipClient is Python software library built on top of PJSIP that together
with an elegant middleware allows for easy development of Client/Server and
Peer-to-Peer Internet communications end-points based on SIP SIMPLE
protocols with rich Presence, Interactive Messaging (IM) and File Transfer
capabilities.
<<
Homepage: http://ag-projects.com/

<<
